The paper deals with the design of testing schemes for identifying a small number of defective items among a large number of items, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The construction of disjunct matrices is a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and combinatorics (cs.CC). The use of error-correcting codes is a topic in coding theory (cs.IT) and information theory (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
